Recent or Planned Changes to Improve Safety

Merisol Antioxidants LLC performs periodic process hazard analyses (safety reviews) of all chemical processes, including the isobutylene alkylation system. Some of the planned or recently completed changes to improve the safety of the isobutylene storage and transfer system are listed below.

1) New bottoms were installed and inspections performed on the isobutylene storage vessels in 2003;
2) External relief valves were installed on the isobutylene pumps to prevent over-pressure and over-temperature in 2003;
3) New higher pressure rated piping and gaskets were installed in isobutylene liquid service piping associated with the storage vessels in 2003;
4) The addition of excess flow valves for the vapor lines connecting the unloading area to the storage vessels are planned for 2004; and
5) Reducing co-located volumes of isobutylene in railcars is planned for 2004.


 Merisol Antioxidants LLC has a continuous improvement philosophy in all safety and environment issues.
